Non-GAAP Financial Measures, and other SEC regulations define and", "bbox": [185.5, 1240.1, 1083.6, 1261.2]}, {"text": "prescribe the conditions for use of certain non-GAAP financial information. Our measure of “Free cash flow”", "bbox": [143.8, 1265.3, 1059.9, 1286.2]}, {"text": "meets the definition of a non-GAAP financial measure. Free cash flow is used in addition to and in conjunction", "bbox": [143.8, 1290.3, 1073.1, 1311.2]}, {"text": "with results presented in accordance with GAAP and free cash flow should not be relied upon to the exclusion of", "bbox": [143.8, 1315.3, 1086.9, 1336.2]}, {"text": "GAAP financial measures. Free cash flow reflects an additional way of viewing our liquidity that, when viewed", "bbox": [143.8, 1340.4, 1077.1, 1361.2]}, {"text": "with our GAAP results, provides a more complete understanding of factors and trends affecting our cash flows.", "bbox": [143.8, 1365.4, 1073.7, 1386.2]}, {"text": "Management strongly encourages shareholders to review our financial statements and publicly-filed reports in", "bbox": [143.8, 1390.4, 1063.7, 1411.2]}, {"text": "their entirety and not to rely on any single financial measure.", "bbox": [143.8, 1415.4, 652.4, 1436.2]}, {"text": "37", "bbox": [608.6, 1465.8, 629.4, 1486.6]}]}